2006-03-01   dok	04:23:11	Denis Oliver Kropp <dok@directfb.org>

	Files:	lib/fusion/call.c (1.4) (+15 -10;)
		systems/x11/x11input.c (1.11) (+2 -0;)
		systems/x11/x11.c (1.8) (+2 -0;)
		systems/x11/primary.c (1.8) (+6 -4;)
		systems/vnc/primary.c (1.4) (+4 -4;)
		systems/sdl/primary.c (1.11) (+13 -14;)
		systems/fbdev/fbdev.c (1.35) (+1 -1;)
		lib/fusion/types.h (1.4) (+14 -5;)
		lib/fusion/call.h (1.4) (+10 -9;)
	
	Added FusionCallExecFlags parameter to fusion_call_execute().
	
	Use the flag FCEF_ONEWAY in the SDL backend to not wait for the
	call being executed, otherwise a deadlock could occur. The return
	value is meaningless anyways. Queued updates will be merged on the
	receiving side (master) to avoid a lag and improve performance.
	
2006-02-22   dok	08:27:02	Denis Oliver Kropp <dok@directfb.org>

	Files:	lib/fusion/fusion.c (1.18) (+1 -1;)
	
	Make compiler happy.
	
2006-02-15   dok	16:17:27	Denis Oliver Kropp <dok@directfb.org>

